
ABOUT
=====

This is a simple interface to add Python's logging module to your code.
Simply import and configure it at the top level and you're ready to go!

EXAMPLE
=======

  import ez.log as logging
  log = logging.setup()
  log.set_level(logging.DEBUG)

  # some time later
  log.debug('oops')
  log.info('hello')
  log.warn('uh oh...')
  log.error('mayday! mayday!')
  log.critical('42 / 0')
